# Platform Sync Architecture

## What Was Built

A full background sync system so the app always renders from **our own DB** and never blocks the UI on live API calls.

### New DB fields on `SocialAccount`
- `lastSuccessfulSyncAt` — when a sync last completed successfully
- `lastSyncAttemptAt` — when we last tried (includes failures)
- `lastSyncStatus` — `"idle" | "syncing" | "success" | "partial" | "error" | "needs_reconnect"`
- `lastSyncError` — error message on failure
- `initialBackfillDone` — true once first-connect backfill is done

### New `sync_jobs` table
Every sync is recorded with: `scope`, `syncType`, `status`, `idempotencyKey`, timing, `errorDetails`, `itemsProcessed`.

